children.text: The loadbearing wall in this area does not have a lintel beam installed, which will result in the frame sagging and possible failure.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 1684 Residential Timber-Framed Construction states in section 6.2.3 Openings, that
'Openings shall be framed with jamb studs and lintels' .
The builder should install a correctly sized lintel beam into this opening in accordance with the engineering and AS1684, prior to works in this area proceeding any further.
